parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the scooter to stall or not start, leaving the rider stranded, which can lead to accidents or injuries, especially in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The scooter stalls or does not start
the fuel pump does not engage
the scooter loses power and decelerates rapidly
the fuel pump makes a decreased or no sound
the scooter can only be restarted after cooling down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or refuse to start, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents, especially in high-traffic areas or when operating in extreme temperatures.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or refuses to start
the fuel pump fails to operate
the fuel pump makes unusual sounds or does not make any sound
the vehicle restarts after a period of time
the fuel pump takes longer than usual to start running.
